  "prompt": "Why do I look very hot in the mirror, but pretty bad in pictures?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why you might look different in mirrors versus photos:\n\n1. Mirror reflection\n- Mirrors show a reversed image\n- You're used to seeing yourself this way\n- You see yourself from a slightly different angle\n\n2. Lighting differences\n- Mirrors usually have more flattering, soft lighting\n- Photos can have harsh, unflattering light\n- Camera flash can create unflattering shadows\n\n3. Camera lens distortion\n- Different camera lenses can alter your appearance\n- Wide-angle lenses can make features look slightly different\n- Phone cameras can sometimes create slight distortions\n\n4. Psychological factors\n- In the mirror, you're moving and seeing yourself dynamically\n- Photos capture a static moment\n- You're more critical of photo images\n\n5. Camera angle\n- Photos are often taken from a less flattering angle\n- Mirror reflection allows you to adjust your pose\n\n6. Quality of camera\n- Lower quality cameras can create less flattering images\n- Professional cameras and good lighting can capture more accurate representations\n\nTips to look better in photos:\n- Find your best angles\n- Practice posing\n- Use good lighting\n- Relax and smile naturally\n\nRemember, you likely look better in photos than you think!",
